'''Industrial Scripts''' [http://www.industrialscripts.co.uk (Industrial Scripts)] is a UK-based [[screenwriting]] website and script consultancy.<ref>Scriptwriting in the UK. Danny Stack (2010). Available http://dannystack.blogspot.com/2010/04/script-reading-round-up.html Last Accessed 13 August 2010</ref><ref>Scriptwriting in the UK. Danny Stack (2010) Available: http://dannystack.blogspot.com/2009/11/effective-script-reading.html</ref><ref>Linked In Company Profile. Industrial Scripts (2010) Available: http://www.linkedin.com/companies/industrial-scripts</ref><ref>Script Writer Training Review (2010) Available: http://www.scriptwritertraining.com/</ref><ref>Screen South Website. News Articles. Available from: http://www.screensouth.org/newsarticle.aspx?newsid=1784</ref> Its primary aim is to provide script consultancy services, through a team of established script readers. Script reading services allow directors, production companies and screenwriters (both established and amateur) to have screenplays analysed, examining their marketability, suitability for production, and potential for further development.

==History and Organization==
Industrial Scripts was founded in early 2010, and is a small company, operating from its London-based offices. Individuals currently working within the British film and television industries,<ref>UK Screen Website. (2010) Available from: http://www.ukscreen.com/crew/industrial Last accessed 13 August 2010</ref> including Evan-Leighton Davis,<ref>Industrial Scripts Website. (2010) Available: http://industrialscripts.co.uk/script-reader-uk Last Accessed 13 August 2010/</ref><ref>International Movie Data Base. (2010). Evan Leighton-Davis. Available: https://www.imdb.com/name/nm3326939. Last accessed 13 August 2010./</ref> Toby Garfath,<ref>Industrial Scripts Website (2010)Available: http://industrialscripts.co.uk/script-reader-uk Last accessed 13 August 2010/</ref> and Daisy Allsop <ref>International Movie Data Base. Daisy Allsop. Available: https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1457790 Last accessed 13 August 2010/</ref> are responsible for all of Industrial Script's consultancy work. Since its inception, Industrial Scripts has provided script feedback, analysis and reading services for a variety of notable production companies and organizations, including [[BBC Films]], Dan Films, [[Ealing Studios]], [[Warner Bros.]], [[Ridley Scott|Scott Free Films]] and [[Optimum Releasing]].<ref>UK Screen Website (2010) Available:http://www.ukscreen.com/crew/industrial Last accessed 15 August 2010</ref>

==Development and Changes==
Notable recent changes to the company include the expansion and development of services geared towards amateur and aspiring film-makers and writers, including monthly training courses held in 'Effective Script Reading' and 'Making The Low Budget Feature Film.' <ref>Screen South Website. News Articles. Available from: http://www.screensouth.org/newsarticle.aspx?newsid=1784 Last accessed 13 August 2010</ref> The website has recently been expanded to include a feature called 'The Insider Interviews', where interviews  <ref>Industrial Scripts Website. The Insider Interviews (2010) Available at: http://industrialscripts.co.uk/british-film-interviews/</ref>  with individuals currently working in the British film industry <ref>International Movie Database. David Scinto. (2010)Available: https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0778476 Last accessed 13 August 2010 /</ref><ref>International Movie Data Base. Alexei Boltho. (2010) Available: https://www.imdb.com/name/nm3053108 Last accessed 13 August 2010/</ref> can be viewed. These include writer/director [[Stuart Hazeldine]], Alexei Boltho of [[Paramount Pictures|Paramount]] and screenwriter David Scinto.

