{{distinguish|Mok language (Papua New Guinea)}} {{Infobox language |name=Mok |nativename= |region=[[Shan State]], [[Myanmar]] and [[Lampang]], [[Thailand]] |speakers=? |date=2018 |ref=<ref name="Hall2018"/> |familycolor=Austro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Palaungic languages|Palaungic]] |fam3=[[Angkuic languages|Angkuic]] |fam4= |iso3=mqt |glotto=mokk1243 |glottorefname=Mok }}
'''Mok''', also known as Amok<ref>OLAC Resources in and about the Mok Language, www.language-archives.org/language.php/mqt.</ref>, Hsen-Hsum, and Muak, is an [[Angkuic languages|Angkuic]] language spoken in [[Shan State]], [[Myanmar]]<ref name="Hall2018"/> and in [[Lampang Province]], [[Thailand]]. In Lampang Province, Thailand, 7 speakers were reported by Wurm & Hattori (1981).
