{{Infobox person | name = Olga Meyer | image = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date |1930|8|8|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Fana]], Norway | death_date = {{Death date and age |2018|8|27|1930|8|8|df=y}} | death_place = [[Oslo]], Norway | nationality = Norwegian | occupation = [[Journalist]] and [[radio host]] }}
'''Olga Meyer''' (8 August 1930 &ndash; 27 August 2018) was a Norwegian journalist and radio host.
She was born in [[Fana]], and was educated as schoolteacher from [[Volda University College|Volda Teachers' College]]. She was assigned with [[NRK]] Radio from 1969. Programs she worked with in include ''Kvardagen'', ''Forbrukaren har ordet'', ''På direkten'', ''{{ill|Sånn er livet|no}}'', ''Sølvsuper'' and ''{{ill|Nitimen|no}}''. She was awarded {{ill|Kringkastingsprisen|no}} in 1981, and was named honorary member of [[Noregs Mållag]] in 2000.<ref name=allkunne>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Olga Meyer |first= |last= |editor-first=Ottar |editor-last=Grepstad |editor-link=Ottar Grepstad |encyclopedia=Allkunne |publisher=Nynorsk kultursentrum |location= |url= https://www.allkunne.no/framside/biografiar/m/olga-meyer/96/731/ |language=Norwegian|accessdate=4 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nm.no/tekst.cfm?path=10197,10201,10208&id=1957 |title=Olga Meyer og Torolv Hesthamar er nye heidersmedlemer i Noregs Mållag |publisher=[[Noregs Mållag]] |language=Norwegian|accessdate=4 September 2018}}</ref>
She died in [[Oslo]] in 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://mediejobb.no/nrk-nitimen-olga-meyer/den-mangearige-nrk-journalisten-olga-meyer-er-dod/330478 |title=Den mangeårige NRK-journalisten Olga Meyer er død |website=mediejobb.no |language=Norwegian|accessdate=4 September 2018}}</ref>
==Selected works== *''Dyrehistorier i Nitimen'' (1996)
